All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Agent
Agent class that inherits from the Worker interface.
AgentControllable
Interface that defines the operations controllable by an agent.
AgentDBImplementation
This class provides implementation for the AgentControllable interface and handles database operations related to agents.
DBConnectionController
This class is used to connect with the database
DBConnectionController
The DBConnectionController class is responsible for managing the database connection.
Facility
Facility class interface.
Loginable
Interface that defines operations related to login functionality.
LoginDBImplementation
The LoginDBImplementation class provides an implementation of the Loginable interface and handles database operations related to user login and worker information.
Overseer
Overseer class that inherits from the Worker interface.
OverseerControllable
Interface that defines the operations controllable by an overseer.
OverseerDBImplementation
Implements the functionality for managing Overseer objects in the database.
RotatedLabel
Class used to rotate JLabels, inherits from JLabel.
Scientific
Scientific class that represents a worker with a scientific background.
ScientificControllable
Interface that defines the operations controllable by a scientist.
ScientificDBImplementation
This class provides an implementation of the ScientificControllable interface for managing scientific workers in a database.
SCP
SCP class that represents a Secure Containment Procedure.
Worker
Worker class used for different users.
